    <exploration>
      <introduction>
        <p>
          Consider the function <m>w=f(x,y,z)=x^2+z^2</m>. This function has an input <m>y</m>, but notice that changing the input <m>y</m> does not change the output of the function. This means that when <m>y=0</m> you can draw one curve. When <m>y=1</m>, you should draw the same curve. When <m>y=2</m>, again you draw the same curve, etc.
        </p>
